byLineInfo.name: Visit the Up To Par Covers Store

features: MADE IN U.S.A - All our products are proudly made in U.S.A and are made with high quality marine grade vinyl and top stitched for extra strength and to help prevent water from getting through. All our products are made to order. We politely ask for up to 5 business days to produce and ship.
Free samples of our colors are available by request. Just let us know what colors you would like to see. The colors on your screen may differ from what you actually receive.

This seat cover is designed specifically for the model cart listed in the title and in the pictures of this listing. They are designed to fit the original unaltered seating. If your cart does not match the title or pictures, it will not fit your seating. If you do not see your cart here, we have plenty of other options in our store. Click on our logo to see more options. You may also contact us and send pictures of your cart to help verify what you may need.

DIY - Easy to Install - This is a full replacement seat cover. They are designed to be stapled on. There will be enough material to wrap under the seat and staple. Mostly all pictures you see of our products are all customer done and a lot of our customers have zero to very little experience in upholstery work.
When your cart is complete. Please help us by reviewing the product. Send us pictures of your work. We love to see our products on your cart.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Know correct year of cart and confidence in your handy man or handy woman's abilities.
reviews.reviewText: We actually had a roll of material to use before I ran across this listing on Amazon. My concerns were getting a close fit because of the age of the cart, 1992, and possibly wood damage from age and water. We also ordered a manual hand stapler kit with staple remover and staples. Good instructions but the best part was " FOR BEST RESULTS GET A PROFESSIONAL". Well, I'm no professional and this was my first attempt at any kind of seat repair. T50 staples were used. The hardest part was actually removing the old staples. Think I counted about a zillion of them. Fit and finish were perfect on bench seat and back rests. Totally satisfied with this product and the results I got!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent and easy quality.
reviews.reviewText: This is a good quality, vinyl seat cover! The color I chose is "Cornerstone". I went with that 'cause I plan on painting the cart a darker color eventually. This is for a 1999 Club Car DS. I didn't remove the original covers, just simply installed over them. I did it by myself with a screw driver, a socket and ratchet, and a staple gun. Took about an hour and a half, with a day in between 'cause I chose to paint the seat backs while I had them off. I do recommend leaving the covers out in the sun for a while before working with them, they come folded up and this helps the creases go away easier. Well worth the money in you wanna freshen up those old worn golf cart seats.
